== Roasted Vegetables ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Toss Brussels sprouts and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

== Mashed Potatoes ==

While veggies roast, dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces.

> TIP: For a smoother texture, peel potatoes first.

Place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to #pot{}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to mash.

== Chicken ==

While potatoes cook, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, strip @rosemary{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves until you have 2 tsp (3 tsp for 4 servings).

> Swap in chicken or steak for pork. Cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook steak to desired doneness, 5-7 minutes per side.

== Pan Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add minced onion and chopped rosemary. Cook, stirring often, until onion is softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @chicken stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup} (1⁄3 cup for 4 servings). Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat and stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted.

== Mashed Potatoes Finish ==

Return pot with drained potatoes to medium-low heat. Add @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} and @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Slice chicken crosswise.

> Thinly slice chicken or steak against the grain.

Divide chicken, mashed potatoes, and veggies between plates. Top chicken with sauce and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.